package client

// art.go — pixel-art renderer and menu art for the Loba start-menu screen.
//
// Rendering techniques:
//   - Half-block (▀/▄): each terminal row encodes two pixel rows.
//   - Braille (⠁–⣿): each terminal cell encodes a 2×4 pixel block.
//
// LOBA wordmark: hand-crafted pixel grid, 10 px tall (5 terminal rows via
// half-block), sunset gradient per row (magenta→pink→orange).
//
// Hot dog logo: half-block sprite, 24 px wide × 24 px tall (12 terminal rows).
// Generated by tools/png2sprite; braille technique is preserved in RenderBrailleSprite
// for future line-art use.

import (
	"strings"

	"github.com/charmbracelet/lipgloss"

	"github.com/zwenger/TUI-LOBA/internal/protocol"
)

